988
01:00:47,409 --> 01:00:52,779
My sports book shall
be called, ASAP!

989
01:00:52,780 --> 01:00:56,049
All Serious Action Players!
Completely legal.

990
01:00:56,050 --> 01:00:58,253
- Oh, that's incredible.
- Look at the eight horse.

991
01:00:58,254 --> 01:01:00,821
Where the heck did she come from?
She's going to mess up my Perfecta.

992
01:01:00,822 --> 01:01:03,424
Curacao, that's a beautiful
island in the Caribbean, right?

993
01:01:03,425 --> 01:01:06,228
- Beautiful, legit island.
- Oh... Oh, God.

994
01:01:08,731 --> 01:01:10,931
- Come on...
- You got it...

995
01:01:10,932 --> 01:01:12,733
- You got it, you got it...
- Yes!

996
01:01:12,734 --> 01:01:14,202
- There it goes!
- Yes! Yes!

997
01:01:14,203 --> 01:01:16,108
Oh, yes!

998
01:01:20,108 --> 01:01:23,343
- Yes! Yes!
- How did you do that?

999
01:01:23,344 --> 01:01:25,512
How'd you pick the eight horse to win?
She looked like absolute shit to me.

1000
01:01:25,513 --> 01:01:27,983
That was like so surreal and
yesterday it was Cleveland.

1001
01:01:27,984 --> 01:01:31,785
- You're back. You are back.
- Two weeks ago, she looked like a mess.

1002
01:01:31,786 --> 01:01:34,123
But I thought she was starting to get
her head around the whole thing.

1003
01:01:34,124 --> 01:01:39,893
Ruby Lane, Ruby Lane.
Ruby Lane...

1004
01:01:39,894 --> 01:01:41,895
What does Dink think?

1005
01:01:41,896 --> 01:01:46,200
Well, I'm not really
talking to Dink right now.

1006
01:01:46,201 --> 01:01:49,870
Beth, you made a lot of money
in the last couple of months.

1007
01:01:49,871 --> 01:01:52,874
- Why don't you just stay here with me?
- And do what?

1008
01:01:52,875 --> 01:01:55,010
Continue to have the completely fantastic
time we've been having together.

1009
01:01:56,010 --> 01:02:00,480
Look, Jeremy, I don't think you realize what
a huge deal this Curacao thing is for me.

1010
01:02:00,481 --> 01:02:05,085
I mean, I'm going to actually
be in charge of something.

1011
01:02:05,086 --> 01:02:06,855
Something that's going to
take you someplace else.

1012
01:02:06,856 --> 01:02:10,795
Yeah, but I'll come back.
I'll miss you.

1013
01:02:12,795 --> 01:02:15,062
- So, what about...
- Otis. I know.

1014
01:02:15,063 --> 01:02:17,497
I have to find somewhere
for him to stay.

1015
01:02:17,498 --> 01:02:19,902
I'll take care of Otis. I don't
want him to stay with strangers.

1016
01:02:19,903 --> 01:02:21,435
- Really?
- Yeah.

1017
01:02:21,436 --> 01:02:24,071
Oh, my God, that would be great.
He loves you.

1018
01:02:24,072 --> 01:02:25,907
- You know that, right?
- And I love him.

1019
01:02:25,908 --> 01:02:31,444
Aww...
Otis, you lucky dog.

1020
01:02:31,445 --> 01:02:35,183
Now my only problem is finding
someone to do my pay and collects.

1021
01:02:35,184 --> 01:02:38,518
Hey. You could do that too.

1022
01:02:38,519 --> 01:02:40,488
- Me?
- Yeah.

1023
01:02:40,489 --> 01:02:43,124
You can keep my cut and
feed Otis, and we're even.

1024
01:02:43,125 --> 01:02:45,259
It's easy money.

1025
01:02:45,260 --> 01:02:47,568
I'll talk you through
the whole thing.

1026
01:02:53,568 --> 01:02:55,335
Hi, Dave.

1027
01:02:55,336 --> 01:02:58,313
This is Jeremy...

1028
01:03:05,313 --> 01:03:07,952
Bye.

1029
01:03:09,952 --> 01:03:12,085
So, what's your number?

1030
01:03:12,086 --> 01:03:14,120
I'm gonna have a plain burger.

1031
01:03:14,121 --> 01:03:16,357
No bun, no sauce,
no nothing on it.

1032
01:03:16,358 --> 01:03:17,892
I know.

1033
01:03:17,893 --> 01:03:19,425
It had some barbecue sauce
on it last time,

1034
01:03:19,426 --> 01:03:21,463
and I really don't want
to go through that again.

1035
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:25,600
So, a very plain burger and
nothing else, and a regular Coke.

1036
01:03:25,601 --> 01:03:27,935
- Got it.
- Thanks.

1037
01:03:27,936 --> 01:03:30,437
- Stomach?
- Oh, yeah.

1038
01:03:30,438 --> 01:03:33,640
Why? What's on your mind?
You're doing so good.

1039
01:03:33,641 --> 01:03:37,178
Yeah, yeah. I'm just a
little worried about Beth.

1040
01:03:37,179 --> 01:03:39,346
Dink.

1041
01:03:39,347 --> 01:03:41,616
She's working for that
maniac Rosie in New York.

1042
01:03:41,617 --> 01:03:45,919
I blew up at her and now
she's not calling me back.

1043
01:03:45,920 --> 01:03:47,922
Look, I wasn't going to say
anything, but do you notice

1044
01:03:47,923 --> 01:03:51,125
when Beth is around, you
were doing a lot of losing.

1045
01:03:51,126 --> 01:03:54,462
And now that she's gone,
you're doing really good.

1046
01:03:54,463 --> 01:03:57,364
Hey, if anyone's
the jinx, it's Beth.

1047
01:03:57,365 --> 01:03:59,366
But I owe her.

1048
01:03:59,367 --> 01:04:01,201
Owe her for what?

1049
01:04:01,202 --> 01:04:03,571
I owe her for messing
everything up.

1050
01:04:03,572 --> 01:04:07,508
I usually just think about how
much money I could've made

1051
01:04:07,509 --> 01:04:10,377
if I'd just focused a little
bit more when I was younger.

1052
01:04:10,378 --> 01:04:12,581
And I usually give myself
a hard time about it.

1053
01:04:12,582 --> 01:04:17,051
But now, I'm looking at all the
things I've got to do instead.

1054
01:04:17,052 --> 01:04:19,319
I got to be with you.

1055
01:04:19,320 --> 01:04:22,290
And it's not like
I don't appreciate you

1056
01:04:22,291 --> 01:04:24,658
on a daily basis, because I do.

1057
01:04:24,659 --> 01:04:27,528
But for the first time,
since our wedding,

1058
01:04:27,529 --> 01:04:31,000
I look at my situation, and I'm looking
at it from an oddsmaker's perspective.

1059
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:34,672
And I am a really lucky guy.

1060
01:04:37,672 --> 01:04:41,274
And to be honest, a big part
of that is because of Beth.

1061
01:04:41,275 --> 01:04:44,210
Hey, how you doin'?

1062
01:04:44,211 --> 01:04:46,379
I wanted to say hi.

1063
01:04:46,380 --> 01:04:48,716
And tell you that, um,
I hope you don't think

1064
01:04:48,717 --> 01:04:51,584
that we're in some kind of fight,
because I don't think that.

1065
01:04:51,585 --> 01:04:53,220
And, just wanted to call...

1066
01:04:53,221 --> 01:04:55,689
...and see
how you're doing.

1067
01:04:55,690 --> 01:04:58,426
Um, give me a shout
if you have a minute.

1068
01:04:58,427 --> 01:05:01,662
And I also wanted you to
know that I'm not mad

1069
01:05:01,663 --> 01:05:04,132
that you're working
for Rosie in New York.

1070
01:05:04,133 --> 01:05:06,299
So, that's about it.

1071
01:05:06,300 --> 01:05:08,234
Call me, I'm at the office,

1072
01:05:08,235 --> 01:05:12,305
and hope you're OK
and having fun.

1073
01:05:12,306 --> 01:05:14,579
OK, bye.

1074
01:05:18,579 --> 01:05:20,413
Hello, ASAP?

1075
01:05:20,414 --> 01:05:23,452
- Hello, sport?
- Hello, ASAP?

1076
01:05:25,219 --> 01:05:27,388
Can you turn the music off!

1077
01:05:27,389 --> 01:05:30,256
Hey, there are phones ringing
and you're playing video games

1078
01:05:30,257 --> 01:05:32,292
and... what? Doing coke?!

1079
01:05:32,293 --> 01:05:34,462
Oh, my God,
what are they doing here?

1080
01:05:34,463 --> 01:05:36,696
All the plumbing at their
place is backing up.

1081
01:05:36,697 --> 01:05:39,232
What, so you just move them out
of the brothel and into here?

1082
01:05:39,233 --> 01:05:41,036
If you think about it
for two seconds, Beth,

1083
01:05:41,037 --> 01:05:44,171
you'll see this saves time
and money for everybody.

1084
01:05:44,172 --> 01:05:46,009
Hey! Where've
you been for four days?

1085
01:05:47,009 --> 01:05:50,410
Bethy, I have been in love.
What is wrong with me?

1086
01:05:50,411 --> 01:05:53,314
Why is it that all of
my dreams come true?

1087
01:05:53,315 --> 01:05:55,150
Look at this line
here on Cleveland.

1088
01:05:55,151 --> 01:05:57,417
This is terrible.
Who made this line?

1089
01:05:57,418 --> 01:06:00,421
Bob made it. Look, Rosie,
when you disappear,

1090
01:06:00,422 --> 01:06:03,323
these fucking assholes you brought
down here just make shitty lines,

1091
01:06:03,324 --> 01:06:07,261
do coke, have sex with 17 year
olds, and steal from you.

1092
01:06:07,262 --> 01:06:09,430
Easy. Beth,
these are my friends.

1093
01:06:09,431 --> 01:06:11,665
Rosie, this was your big move.

1094
01:06:11,666 --> 01:06:14,201
The only important thing you've
ever done in your whole life,

1095
01:06:14,202 --> 01:06:17,203
and you're letting it fucking disintegrate!
What is wrong with you?!

1096
01:06:17,204 --> 01:06:20,107
Beth, you are the gum that
holds this all together.

1097
01:06:20,108 --> 01:06:23,544
You put up with a lot, and you
deserve respect for that.

1098
01:06:23,545 --> 01:06:27,047
I'm giving a raise to $5,000
a week, effective last week.

1099
01:06:27,048 --> 01:06:29,186
But just do not tell anybody.

1100
01:06:31,186 --> 01:06:33,319
All right, check on Motown!

1101
01:06:33,320 --> 01:06:37,625
Check on the Cuban! Somebody
call HBC and give 20 dimes to...

1102
01:06:37,626 --> 01:06:39,097
Fuck! We're getting
buried on this game!

1103
01:06:42,097 --> 01:06:44,397
Hello?

1104
01:06:44,398 --> 01:06:46,534
Did you know that
Otis runs in his sleep?

1105
01:06:46,535 --> 01:06:49,803
Yes.

1106
01:06:49,804 --> 01:06:55,408
Jeremy, how are you?
I miss you.

1107
01:06:55,409 --> 01:06:58,449
- You miss me?
- Of course I do.

1108
01:07:00,449 --> 01:07:02,583
Could you tell me
something normal?

1109
01:07:02,584 --> 01:07:04,151
Sure, like what?

1110
01:07:04,152 --> 01:07:07,187
I don't know, about
your day? Anything?

1111
01:07:07,188 --> 01:07:09,622
Have you checked
Greenberg's bets lately?

1112
01:07:09,623 --> 01:07:11,759
No.

1113
01:07:11,760 --> 01:07:13,828
He and his friends
are losing finally.

1114
01:07:13,829 --> 01:07:16,596
And big time,
like 75 grand worth.

1115
01:07:16,597 --> 01:07:18,598
Really? That's nice.

1116
01:07:18,599 --> 01:07:22,403
I can't get any of those
guys on the phone, though.

1117
01:07:22,404 --> 01:07:25,138
You're their only action,
and they're idiot addicts.

1118
01:07:25,139 --> 01:07:26,775
They'll call.

1119
01:07:30,846 --> 01:07:33,747
I gotta go.

1120
01:07:33,748 --> 01:07:36,616
Rosie's friends are
destroying the place.

1121
01:07:36,617 --> 01:07:40,821
Don't worry about Greenberg.

1122
01:07:40,822 --> 01:07:46,161
146, 152, 155 total.

1123
01:07:50,398 --> 01:07:54,273
...Minus 13. No, leave it
just at 7 and a half flat.

1124
01:07:58,273 --> 01:08:00,473
Rosie, can you turn it down?!

1125
01:08:00,474 --> 01:08:04,745
I can't Beth. This song
is the rhythm of victory!

1126
01:08:04,746 --> 01:08:08,265
Don't let the rhythm
not get you and move!

1127
01:08:23,265 --> 01:08:27,468
Beth, Dave Greenberg here.
We got a problem.

1128
01:08:27,469 --> 01:08:30,537
I, uh... got into some trouble
a couple of years ago.

1129
01:08:30,538 --> 01:08:33,840
It's a long story, but my
parole officer called me in.

1130
01:08:33,841 --> 01:08:38,312
And he wants to know about you
and who's running your office.

1131
01:08:38,313 --> 01:08:40,813
Now, don't worry
I didn't give you up,

1132
01:08:40,814 --> 01:08:43,216
but this is a fucking mess.

1133
01:08:43,217 --> 01:08:44,951
He's got all the
numbers from my phone,

1134
01:08:44,952 --> 01:08:45,921
including yours and Jeremy's.

1135
01:08:45,922 --> 01:08:50,291
So, if he calls...
just play dumb.

1136
01:08:50,292 --> 01:08:52,792
But whatever you do,
don't call me.

1137
01:08:52,793 --> 01:08:55,965
I'll call you.

1138
01:08:56,965 --> 01:08:59,465
It's not a big deal. The
Seattle game's about to start.

1139
01:08:59,466 --> 01:09:01,367
Why don't you go upstairs?

1140
01:09:01,368 --> 01:09:02,908
It's...

1141
01:09:06,908 --> 01:09:09,742
My life is over,
even if I don't go to jail.

1142
01:09:09,743 --> 01:09:11,311
If I get arrested
on a felony charge,

1143
01:09:11,312 --> 01:09:13,278
I am done forever
as a journalist.

1144
01:09:13,279 --> 01:09:15,684
I'm 98 percent sure that
Dave Greenberg is lying.

1145
01:09:15,685 --> 01:09:17,850
He just doesn't want to pay,
or he can't pay.

1146
01:09:17,851 --> 01:09:20,955
If Dave Greenberg has a parole
officer, it does seem plausible

1147
01:09:20,956 --> 01:09:23,792
that he would want to know who Dave's
bookie is, and that Dave would tell him.

1148
01:09:23,793 --> 01:09:27,827
Look! I'm going to...

1149
01:09:27,828 --> 01:09:30,230
I'm going to call Dink.

1150
01:09:30,231 --> 01:09:31,863
Wait, what? You're
going to call Dink?

1151
01:09:31,864 --> 01:09:33,801
You said you haven't
been talking to him.

1152
01:09:33,802 --> 01:09:38,339
I haven't.
But I'll just... call him.

1153
01:09:38,340 --> 01:09:39,774
- I'll call you back.
- No, no! No.

1154
01:09:39,775 --> 01:09:42,343
Do not call me back.
I am at a payphone.

1155
01:09:42,344 --> 01:09:43,944
Do not call
my phone from Curacao,

1156
01:09:43,945 --> 01:09:46,580
the gambling mecca
of the Caribbean!

1157
01:09:46,581 --> 01:09:49,883
No, no. It's not,
not a big deal.

1158
01:09:49,884 --> 01:09:51,618
That's just Rosie saying that,

1159
01:09:51,619 --> 01:09:53,320
so you'll forget about it
and go back to work.

1160
01:09:53,321 --> 01:09:56,489
Look, I'm sorry
that I abandoned you.

1161
01:09:56,490 --> 01:09:58,926
Now will you please
calm down and talk to me...

1162
01:09:58,927 --> 01:10:01,661
I appreciate your apology.

1163
01:10:01,662 --> 01:10:05,032
But I want you to know this is
a very serious situation, OK?

1164
01:10:05,033 --> 01:10:10,703
You had a felon,
paroled, the FBI...

1165
01:10:10,704 --> 01:10:13,674
I've seen go down just
like this in the past,

1166
01:10:13,675 --> 01:10:16,977
and I'm not just talking
about my circumstances, OK?

1167
01:10:16,978 --> 01:10:19,947
This is a very big problem.

1168
01:10:19,948 --> 01:10:22,515
How is it down there?

1169
01:10:22,516 --> 01:10:25,286
What, what the heck's going on?

1170
01:10:25,287 --> 01:10:28,054
I'm earning $5,000 a week.

1171
01:10:28,055 --> 01:10:29,957
Beth, you never
cared about money.

1172
01:10:29,958 --> 01:10:32,693
I thought you went down there
because it's paradise?

1173
01:10:32,694 --> 01:10:35,295
Is it paradise?

1174
01:10:35,296 --> 01:10:38,698
- No.
- Don't cry.

1175
01:10:38,699 --> 01:10:41,301
Don't cry, just...

1176
01:10:41,302 --> 01:10:44,371
Listen to me, Beth. You are the
book in this New York thing.

1177
01:10:44,372 --> 01:10:46,572
You have got to take
care of your people.

1178
01:10:46,573 --> 01:10:49,943
Your decisions are no longer
just about you anymore.

1179
01:10:49,944 --> 01:10:53,980
- You have to handle this.
- But I don't know how to handle it.

1180
01:10:53,981 --> 01:10:58,021
Yes you do, or you will.

1181
01:11:01,021 --> 01:11:02,989
Hold on one second.

1182
01:11:02,990 --> 01:11:07,594
Hey Beth?

1183
01:11:07,595 --> 01:11:10,997
Look, it's Dink's mom's
birthday on Thursday.

1184
01:11:10,998 --> 01:11:14,468
She was going to come out to Vegas, but she...
she hates flying.

1185
01:11:14,469 --> 01:11:16,404
So, if we come out to
New York, she doesn't

1186
01:11:16,405 --> 01:11:18,805
have to come out here for
her birthday, which...

1187
01:11:18,806 --> 01:11:20,907
- ...she'd love, right honey?
- Yeah.

1188
01:11:20,908 --> 01:11:23,846
We could meet you there.

1189
01:11:25,846 --> 01:11:28,587
You'd... You'd help me?

1190
01:11:32,587 --> 01:11:35,726
Yes, we'll help you help Jeremy.

1191
01:11:38,726 --> 01:11:43,563
Hey, you know when you don't need
to be taken care of anymore?

1192
01:11:43,564 --> 01:11:47,041
It's when you decide to start
taking care of someone else.

1193
01:11:53,041 --> 01:11:54,747
You still there Beth?

1194
01:11:58,747 --> 01:12:00,480
Beth, you're being crazy.

1195
01:12:00,481 --> 01:12:03,450
It's $75,000 this idiot
Greenberg owes me.

1196
01:12:03,451 --> 01:12:06,687
Who cares? I need you here.
I forgive you the Greenberg.

1197
01:12:06,688 --> 01:12:08,755
A clean slate,
you owe me nothing.

1198
01:12:08,756 --> 01:12:10,891
- But you have to stay.
- It's not about the money.

1199
01:12:10,892 --> 01:12:13,693
Well, what's it about?
Jeremy the non-boyfriend?

1200
01:12:13,694 --> 01:12:16,996
Jeremy may be in huge
trouble because of me.

1201
01:12:16,997 --> 01:12:19,967
He chose to do something not completely
